metadata.description:
The second phase of Yotos interactive maths cards. These six cards continue to develop childrens fundamental mathematical skills, helping them to navigate the world around them. 

Through a wide range of interactive activities, which utilise the Yoto Players display to provide a unique combination of auditory and visual learning, children from age 5+ can build on their maths skills in six different areas; number recognition to 100, counting in 2s, 5s and 10s (skip-counting), fractions, multiplication and division. Activities will play in a random order every time to encourage kids to return to the cards again and again to build their mathematical knowledge and give them the tools they need to develop their confidence
